 If you renew it after the expiry date, you will have to apply for a temporary driving licence at an additional cost while waiting for your new driving licence to be issued. ALSO READ: You can’t get fined for your backed-logged driver’s licence card ALSO READ: 10 Most common traffic fines and what they will cost you You will undergo eye testing and your fingerprints will be taken. Alternatively, you can have your eyes tested by an optometrist and submit the report at the DLTC. If your sight has worsened from the date on which your licence was issued, new conditions will be attached to your licence.